<p class="c2 c4">
  <span class="c1 c20"></span>
</p>
<p class="c2">
  <span class="c6">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;POWERCOMPUTERS shall, subject to the provisions of this agreement hereof provide return to base Repair, Maintenance and support services for the equipment as identified more specifically in the equipment schedule annexed to this agreement at POWERCOMPUTERS is offices. For the fee set forth in the equipment schedule, POWERCOMPUTERS shall, by its authorized representatives, inspect and maintain in operating condition, the equipment itemized or provide such other services as described in the equipment schedule. If the service plan includes preventive maintenance, such preventive maintenance will be provided as POWERCOMPUTERS deems necessary. POWERCOMPUTERS may provide any preventive maintenance at the same time as POWERCOMPUTERS is providing other service on the covered equipment. Negotiated and agreed on between the parties.</span>
</p>
<p class="c2 c4">
  <span class="c6"></span>
</p>
<p class="c2 c4">
  <span class="c6"> -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The charge for AMC is <strong>Tsh <?=formatN($amount)?></strong> Per device inc. Vat.</span>
</p>
<p class="c2 c4">
  <span class="c6"></span>
</p>
<p class="c2">
  <span class="c6">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For the purpose of this agreement, working hours are specified as follows:</span>
</p>
<p class="c2 c4">
  <span class="c6"></span>
</p>
<p class="c2">
  <span class="c6">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monday -- Friday &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:8.00 am to 5:00pm</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Saturday&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:9:00am to 1:00pm</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sundays and public Holidays not including. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The client shall bear the costs for shipping/transporting/couriering the product to or from the client before or after servicing or repairs. POWERCOMPUTERS will not be responsible for any damages caused during transit of the product.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The fee for services to be performed here under shall be as set forth on the equipment schedule, or, with respect to the price for service performed on a &quot;time and material&quot; basis, at POWERCOMPUTERS is existing current rates.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless an equipment schedule provides otherwise, subscriber will be invoiced yearly in advance. All invoices for periodic fees are due prior to the commencement date for the applicable fee period and will be non-refundable. For equipment schedules added subsequent to the hereof, POWERCOMPUTERS may prorate its invoice to provide for a common invoice date for all equipment covered. All invoices for work performed on a time and material basis not falling under this contract will be due on a &acirc;&euro;&tilde;Net 30 days basis. All invoices not paid within thirty (30) days of the date due shall bear interest at the rate of two percent (2%) per month on the unpaid balance or the highest rate permitted by law, whichever is less. In the event subscriber fails to pay any invoice when due and POWERCOMPUTERS has provided subscribers three (3) days written notice of such failure, POWERCOMPUTERS may, in addition to any other rights and remedies available to POWERCOMPUTERS, suspend service under this contract and any or all equipment Schedules until subscriber is accounts has no amount more than thirty (30) days past due.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The payments provided for herein are based solely on the value of the goods and services provided and are unrelated to the value of subscriber is property of others located on subscribers premises or within the equipment. The providing of service and/or preventive maintenance does not guarantee the continued or uninterrupted operation of the equipment. In no event shall POWERCOMPUTERS be liable for loss, damage, or destruction of subscriber is property caused by burglary, robbery, fire, flood, loss of or mis-dispensing of funds or other documents or items of value. Nor shall POWERCOMPUTERS be liable for special, incidental, indirect or consequential damages of any kind or nature, whether arising under contract, tort, strict liability, or other form of action, whether or not </span></p><hr style="page-break-before:always;display:none;"><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">7. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As a material consideration for POWERCOMPUTERS entering into this contract the parties agree that if, notwithstanding the foregoing limitations POWERCOMPUTERS has any liability to subscriber, such liability shall in no event exceed the yearly fee specified in the equipment schedule for the equipment or service relative to the event. Subscriber may obtain a greater limitation of liability, if desired, by the payment of an increased annual fee, which shall be negotiated by the parties subsequent to POWERCOMPUTERS is receipt of subscriber is written request therefore.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;POWERCOMPUTERS will not be liable for any delay in providing service that is caused by fire or flood, strikes, labor disturbances, riots, war, insurrection, acts of any governmental entity or the public enemy, delays in non POWERCOMPUTERS transportation, delays in supply and shipping of materials from the manufacturer of third parties, unavailability of fuel or other supplies, or any other cause beyond the reasonable control of POWERCOMPUTERS. In the event of such occurrence, POWERCOMPUTERS is time for performance shall be equitably adjusted.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term of this agreement shall be for the period of agreement set forth above starting on the commencement Date. After the expiry of the initial term, the contract may by an agreement of both parties be renewed for a further period to be agreed on between the parties. POWERCOMPUTERS reserves the right to vary the fees at the time of renewal in order to cater for increases in costs such as (but not limited to) administration expenses, overheads, and economic situations. POWERCOMPUTERS shall no later than thirty (30) days prior to the expiry of the contract notify Subscriber of such expiry date and forward its proposal for renewal. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Either subscriber or POWERCOMPUTERS may give notice of cancellation in writing to the other at least thirty (30) days prior to the expiration of the then current term. in the event of any such renewal period, the fees to be paid by subscriber during such period shall be as set forth in the equipment schedule that is included herein. </span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Except as otherwise set forth in the product service &amp; support Details, the services to be provided for a yearly service fee do not include:</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">a. services required as a result of abuse, misuse, electrical storms, power failures or fluctuations, air conditioning, humidity control or other environmental conditions accidents including breakages or damages due to transportation, failure to follow user maintenance and operating instructions, or the failure or results failure of interconnected equipment not specified on an equipment schedule, including, but not limited to, wiring, conduit;</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">b. consumables items including, but not limited to, media and media accessories, fiscal memory, power supply units, batteries, printer paper, printer cartridges, fiscal booklets film, ribbons, light bulbs.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">c. Services required because of service, inspection, or tampering with equipment including the TRA fiscal seal by non-POWERCOMPUTERS designated personnel, relocation of equipment, changes to configuration, installation of additional features, options or functions; major overhauls, or refurbishing the equipment:</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">d. Equipment programming required over and above that at the time of installation due to change in specifications.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">e. Malfunctions resulting from the use of media, supplies, and / or consumables which are not furnished by POWERCOMPUTERS or which do not meet standards set by the manufacturer.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">f. Services required complying with changes in the regulations of any governmental body or agency.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">If POWERCOMPUTERS determines that the service requested by Subscriber is excluded pursuant to the above, and subscriber requests POWERCOMPUTERS to perform such service, the service will be provided pursuant to paragraph </span></p><hr style="page-break-before:always;display:none;"><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">12. Unless the product service &amp; support Details indicates that parts are included, subscriber will pay POWERCOMPUTERS is then current list price for any replacement parts necessary for the performance of service on equipment. The parts used by POWERCOMPUTERS to perform maintenance and repair service hereunder will either new or equivalent to new. Title to parts shall pass to subscriber when the same are installed by POWERCOMPUTERS. Title to parts that are removed and replaced by POWERCOMPUTERS shall vest in POWERCOMPUTERS at the time removal. No title to any computer programs included in part shall ever pass to subscriber. With respect to such parts that include computers programs, POWERCOMPUTERS grants to subscriber a personal, nonexclusive right to use such computer programs in conjunction with the equipment while subscriber is the rightful possessor of the equipment. Such license extends only to the use of the computer programs in conjunction with specific equipment on which the same are installed. Subscriber agrees not to copy, decompose, reverse engineer, or otherwise modify such computer programs. Computer programs for which a separate charge is normally required by POWERCOMPUTERS are licensed only pursuant to a separate license contract.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">13. Subscriber may from time request that POWERCOMPUTERS provide other services not included in the product service &amp; support details for equipment described on the equipment schedule, or for which no equipment schedule has been completed.POWERCOMPUTERS prevailing standard general support charge will be applicable for these services including but not limited to technical, function, data migration, consulting services, implementation services, support service, reconfiguration service, reporting service. For any pre-sales or post-sales on-site support outside POWERCOMPUTERS offices, which necessitates a visit either to carry out software demonstration, installation, training, reconfiguration, technical support, warranty &amp; post-warranty support, the subscriber will have to additionally make necessary&Acirc;&nbsp; arrangements as well as bear all out-of-pocket expenses related to the visit, including cost of fares, local hotel boarding and lodging, and local transportation additionally, subscriber will be required to pay for the technicians per diem charges, at the prevailing rate, for the duration of his/her stay.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">14. Notices to be provided from one part another shall be deemed sufficient if given in writing and sent by registered mail, postage prepaid, with return receipt requested to the address of such party as reflected herein, or such other address as a party may identify by formal notice to the other party. Any notice so given shall be deemed effective five(5) days after mailing as specified herein.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">15. This agreement supersedes all prior agreements, understandings/ arrangements between POWERCOMPUTERS and the client relating to the subject matter hereof. Only written additions or modifications of any provision of this agreement (signed by duly authorized representatives of both parties) shall be binding.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">16. No part of this contract (whole or part) may be transferred or assigned, without POWERCOMPUTERS is written consent. Contract renewal is based on the last contract ending date. In cases where contracts have not been dully renewed on completion of the of the last contract date, a future renewal may be back dated to the last contract ending date.</span></p><p class="c2 c4"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c6">This contract shall be governed by and interpreted in accordance with the laws of Tanzania. If any dispute shall arise between the parties concerning any matter which is subject of, or arise out of this contract, on the interpretation thereof, the same be referred to arbitration in accordance with act of laws of Tanzania. The dispute shall be referred to the arbitration of two arbitrators, one to be appointed by FTS and the other to be appointed by subscriber. The two arbitrators shall there after appoint an umpire. The arbitration proceedings shall be conducted in, Tanzania. The arbitral award shall be final and binding. Each party shall bear its own costs of arbitration. </span></p>

  <p class="c2 c4">
    <span class="c6"></span>
  </p>
  <p class="c2 c4">
    <span class="c6"> -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For cancellation of the contract you have to give us prior Notice. if <strong>POWERCOMPUTERS</strong> wish to stop the service of this contract it will notify prior to your office also refund the amount of the months left in the contract. if the Client wishes to cancel the contract they have to either provide prior notice via email or letter one month prior the cancellation.</span>
